Claims CLAIMS What is claimed is: 1. An Fc fusion polypeptide comprising: an antibody Fc region or fragment thereof; and (a) a 4-lBBL moiety; (b) a CD70 moiety; (c) a GITRL moiety; (d) an OX40 moiety; (e) a CD40 moiety; or (d) a LIGHT moiety. 2. The polypeptide of claim 1, wherein the 4-lBBL moiety, the CD70 moiety, GITRL moiety, OX40L moiety, CD40L moiety, or LIGHT moiety, is C-terminal to the antibody Fc region or fragment thereof. 3. The polypeptide of claim 1 or 2, wherein the 4-lBBL moiety, the CD70 moiety, GITRL moiety, OX40L moiety, CD40L moiety, or LIGHT moiety, is connected to the antibody Fc region or fragment thereof by a linker. 4. The polypeptide of claim 3, wherein the linker is 15-20 amino acid residues in length. 5. The polypeptide of claim 3 or 4, wherein the linker comprises one or more G 4 S motifs. 6. The polypeptide of claim 5, wherein the linker comprises three G 4 S motifs. 7. The polypeptide of any one of claims 1-6, wherein the (a) 4-lBBL moiety comprises two or more 4-lBBL domains; (b) CD70 moiety comprises two or more CD70 domains; (c) GITRL moiety comprises two or more GITRL domains; (d) OX40L moiety comprises two or more OX40L domains; (e) CD40L moiety two or more CD40L domains; or (f) LIGHT moiety comprises two or more LIGHT domains. 8. The polypeptide of claim 7, wherein the (a) 4-lBBL moiety comprises intra-domain linkers connecting the two or more 4- 1BBL domains; 

 (b) CD70 moiety comprises intra-domain linkers connecting the two or more CD70 domains; (c) GITRL moiety comprises intra-domain linkers connecting the two or more GITRL domains; (d) OX40L moiety comprises intra-domain linkers connecting the two or more OX40L domains; (e) CD40L moiety comprises intra-domain linkers connecting the two or more CD40L domains; or (f) LIGHT moiety comprises intra-domain linkers connecting the two or more LIGHT domains. 9. The polypeptide of claim 8, wherein the intra-domain linkers are 15-20 amino acid residues in length. 10. The polypeptide of claim 9, wherein the intra-domain linkers comprise one or more G 4 S motifs. 11. The polypeptide of claim 10, wherein the intra-domain linker comprises three G 4 S motifs. 12. The polypeptide of any one of claims 7-11, wherein the (a) 4-lBBL moiety comprises three 4-lBBL domains; (b) CD70 moiety comprises three CD70 domains; (c) GITRL moiety comprises three GITRL domains; (d) OX40L moiety comprises three OX40L domains; (e) CD40L moiety comprises three CD40L domains; or (f) LIGHT moiety comprises three LIGHT domains. 13. The polypeptide of any one of claims 7-12, wherein (a) each 4-lBBL domain, independently, comprises an amino acid sequence at least 95% identical to a sequence selected from the group consisting of: (i) amino acid residues 50-254 of SEQ ID NO: 4, (ii) amino acid residues 71-254 of SEQ ID NO: 4; and (iii) amino acid residues 85-254 of SEQ ID NO: 4; 

 (b) each CD70 domain, independently, comprises an amino acid sequence at least 95% identical to the amino acid residues 39-193 of SEQ ID NO: 16; (c) each GITRL domain, independently, comprises an amino acid sequence at least 95% identical to a sequence selected from the group consisting of: (i) amino acid residues 72-199 of SEQ ID NO:29; and (ii) amino acid residues 74-199 of SEQ ID NO:29; (d) each OX40L domain, independently, comprises an amino acid sequence at least 95% identical to the amino acid residues 51-183 of SEQ ID NO: 39; (e) each CD40L domain, independently, comprises an amino acid sequence at least 95% identical to a sequence selected from the group consisting of: (i) amino acid residues 47-261 of SEQ ID NO:48; (ii) amino acid residues 116-261 of SEQ ID NO:48; (iii) amino acid residues 108-261 of SEQ ID NO:48; (iv) amino acid residues 113-261 of SEQ ID NO:48; and (f) each LIGHT domain, independently, comprises an amino acid sequence at least 95% identical to a sequence selected from the group consisting of: (i) amino acid residues 59-240 of SEQ ID NO:58; and (ii) amino acid residues 74-240 of SEQ ID NO: 58. 14. The polypeptide of claim 13, wherein (a) each 4-lBBL domain, independently, comprises an amino acid sequence selected from the group consisting of: (i) amino acid residues 50-254 of SEQ ID NO: 4, (ii) amino acid residues 71-254 of SEQ ID NO: 4; (iii) amino acid residues 85-254 of SEQ ID NO: 4; (b) each CD70 independently, comprises an amino acid sequence consisting of amino acid residues 39-193 of SEQ ID NO: 16; (c) each GITRL domain, independently, comprises an amino acid sequence selected from the group consisting of: (i) amino acid residues 72-199 of SEQ ID NO:29; and (ii) amino acid residues 74-199 of SEQ ID NO:29; (d) each OX40L independently, comprises an amino acid sequence consisting of amino acid residues 51-183 of SEQ ID NO: 39; (e) each CD40L independently, comprising an amino acid sequence consisting of: 

 (i) amino acid residues 47-261 of SEQ ID NO:48; (ii) amino acid residues 116-261 of SEQ ID NO:48; (iii) amino acid residues 108-261 of SEQ ID NO:48; (iv) amino acid residues 113-261 of SEQ ID NO:48; or (f) each LIGHT independently, comprising an amino acid sequence consisting of: (i) amino acid residues 59-240 of SEQ ID NO:58; and (ii) amino acid residues 74-240 of SEQ ID NO: 58. 15. The polypeptide of any one of the preceding claims, wherein the polypeptide agonizes (a) 4- IBB; (b) CD27; (c) GITR; (d) OX40; (e) CD40; or (f) TNFRSF14. 16. The polypeptide of any one of the preceding claims, wherein the antibody Fc region is selected from the group consisting of a human IgGl Fc region, a human IgG2 Fc region, a human IgG3 Fc region, a human IgG4 Fc region, and variants thereof. 17. A Fc-fusion polypeptide comprising a human IgG Fc moiety, or fragment thereof, (a) bound to a set of three human 4-lBBL domains to form a single unbranched polypeptide comprising, in amino- to carboxyl-terminal order, the Fc moiety, a linker, a first 4-lBBL domain, an inter-domain linker, a second 4-lBBL domain, a second inter-domain linker, and a third 4-lBBL domain; (b) bound to a set of three human CD70 domains to form a single unbranched polypeptide comprising, in amino- to carboxyl-terminal order, the Fc moiety, a linker, a first CD70 domain, an inter-domain linker, a second CD70 domain, a second inter-domain linker, and a third CD70 domain; (c) bound to a set of three human GITRL domains to form a single unbranched polypeptide comprising, in amino- to carboxyl-terminal order, the Fc moiety, a linker, a first GITRL domain, an inter-domain linker, a second GITRL domain, a second inter-domain linker, and a third GITRL domain; 

 (d) bound to a set of three human OX40L domains to form a single unbranched polypeptide comprising, in amino- to carboxyl-terminal order, the Fc moiety, a linker, a first OX40L domain, an inter-domain linker, a second OX40L domain, a second inter-domain linker, and a third OX40L domain; (e) bound to a set of three human CD40L domains to form a single unbranched polypeptide comprising, in amino- to carboxyl-terminal order, the Fc moiety, a linker, a first CD40L domain, an inter-domain linker, a second CD40L domain, a second inter-domain linker, and a third CD40L domain; or (f) bound to a set of three human LIGHT domains to form a single unbranched polypeptide comprising, in amino- to carboxyl-terminal order, the Fc moiety, a linker, a first LIGHT domain, an inter-domain linker, a second LIGHT domain, a second inter-domain linker, and a third LIGHT domain. 18. The polypeptide of claim 17, wherein at least one of the linkers are 15-20 amino acid residues in length. 19. The polypeptide of claims 17, wherein at least one of the linkers comprise one or more G 4 S motifs. 20. The polypeptide of claim 19, wherein at least one of the linkers comprises three G 4 S motifs. 21. An Fc-4-lBBL fusion polypeptide comprising SEQ ID NO: 8, an Fc-CD70 fusion polypeptide comprising SEQ ID NO: 18, an Fc-GITRL fusion polypeptide comprising SEQ ID NO:29, an Fc-OX40L fusion polypeptide comprising SEQ ID NO:39, an Fc-CD40L fusion polypeptide comprising SEQ ID NO:48, or an Fc-LIGHT fusion polypeptide comprising SEQ ID NO: 58. 22. A protein comprising (a) two separate Fc-41BBL fusion polypeptides; (b) two separate CD70 fusion polypeptides; (c) two separate GITRL fusion polypeptides; (d) two separate OX40L fusion polypeptides; (e) two separate CD40L fusion polypeptides; or (f) two separate LIGHT fusion polypeptides; 

 of any one of claims 1-12, wherein the polypeptides are dimerized by at least one inter-Fc disulfide bond. 23. The polypeptide of any one of claims 1-22, wherein the polypeptide comprises at least one stabilizing mutation. 24. A composition comprising a polypeptide of any one claims 1-23 and a carrier. 25. The composition of claim 24, which is a sterile composition and/or suitable for intravenous injection. 26. A kit comprising the composition of claim 24 or 25 in a container. 27. A method of treating a cancer in a human patient, the method comprising administering to the patient an effective amount of the (a) Fc-4-lBBL fusion polypeptide; (b) CD70 fusion polypeptide; (c) GITRL fusion polypeptide; (d) OX40L fusion polypeptide; (e) CD40L fusion polypeptide; or (f) LIGHT fusion polypeptide; of any one of claims 1-27. 28. A method of treating an autoimmune disorder in a human patient, the method comprising administering to the patient an effective amount of the (a) Fc-4-lBBL fusion polypeptide; (b) CD70 fusion polypeptide; (c) GITRL fusion polypeptide; (d) OX40L fusion polypeptide; (e) CD40L fusion polypeptide; or (f) LIGHT fusion polypeptide; of any one of claims 1-28. 29. The method of claim 27, further comprising administering an additional antineoplastic agent.
